violence /ˈvaɪələns/

1. N-UNCOUNT Violence is behaviour that is intended to hurt, injure, or kill people. 暴力行为 

例： Twenty people were killed in the violence. 有20人在这起暴力事件中被杀害。 

例： ...domestic violence between husband and wife. …夫妻间的家庭暴力。 

2. N-UNCOUNT If you do or say something with violence , you use a lot of force and energy in doing or saying it, often because you are angry. 激烈 [文学性] 

例： The violence in her tone gave Tyler a shock. 她语气激烈，使泰勒大为震惊。

</div>

